## What Broke
- Auto-scroll to bottom stopped working
- Layout is fucked

## Changes Made (NEED TO REVERT)

### 1. apps/web/src/components/ai-elements/conversation.tsx

**Conversation component** - Added `flex flex-col` to scroll container:
```tsx
// BEFORE
className={cn("relative flex-1 overflow-y-auto overflow-x-hidden", className)}

// AFTER (BROKEN)
className={cn("relative flex-1 overflow-y-auto overflow-x-hidden flex flex-col", className)}
```

**ConversationContent component** - Added min-h-full and spacer div:
```tsx
// BEFORE
<div
  ref={contentRef}
  className={cn("flex flex-col gap-6 px-4 py-6 w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto", className)}
  {...props}
>
  {children}
</div>

// AFTER (BROKEN)
<div
  ref={contentRef}
  className={cn("flex flex-col gap-6 px-4 py-6 w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto min-h-full", className)}
  {...props}
>
  {/* Spacer pushes content to bottom when there's little content */}
  <div className="flex-1" aria-hidden="true" />
  {children}
</div>
```

### 2. apps/web/src/app/session/[id]/session-messages.tsx

Removed overflow-hidden from outer div:
```tsx
// BEFORE
<div className="flex flex-col h-full overflow-hidden">
  <Conversation className="flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-hidden">

// AFTER (BROKEN)  
<div className="flex flex-col h-full">
  <Conversation className="flex-1 min-h-0">
```

## Original Issue Being Fixed
- Messages pushed to top with gap at bottom
- Can't scroll to past messages
- Inconsistent pinning behavior

## Root Cause Analysis Was
The layout hierarchy had conflicting overflow properties and ConversationContent didn't fill space properly.

## To Rollback
Revert all three changes above back to BEFORE state.

